  "prompt": "What does \"recipient name\" mean?",
  "response": "The term \"recipient name\" refers to the name of the individual or entity that is intended to receive something, such as a package, letter, payment, or communication. It is commonly used in contexts such as shipping, banking, and official documents to identify who the items or funds are directed toward. For example, when sending a letter, the recipient name would be the person to whom the letter is addressed. Similarly, in financial transactions, it refers to the name of the person or organization receiving the payment.",
